explains: adj. 职位高的；阶级高的

sentences.en: Some otherwise high-ranking countries had relatively low scores for political representation.
sentences.cn: 一些排名靠前的国家在政治代表权方面得分相对较低。

sentences.en: Already a high-ranking military officer by his teenager years, Lin Shu was engaged to Princess Nihuang.
sentences.cn: 林殊十几岁就当上了高级军官，与霓凰公主订了婚。

sentences.en: Since finishing my studies at Harvard and Oxford, I've watched one friend after another land high-ranking, high-paying Wall Street jobs.
sentences.cn: 自从我完成了哈佛和牛津的学业，我看着一个又一个朋友在华尔街拿到了薪资丰厚的高职。
